            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Edit Jan 12th 2023: I am extremely sad I admitted so many kids with reference to this school so that it prospers and so does my son.  Never thought like  Bullying and teacher missing and education will go for toss. After several Bullying complaints the school , teachers and management have just turned blind eye. Missing teacher and rushing through portion without making sure kids have understood.\nVery very disappointed.\n\n2019: My son is in this school for past 4 years and I am so thankful I went with my inner voice rather then reviews. He ha sbeen very well taken care off when he gets this dust allergy issues  and the school and staff had been so good and approachable. I would recommend this school over any other in that area for their education, approach.\n\nEdit 2022: This review is for this year. I am  a bit disappointed the way the school has handles few things. So I have changed my review based on how the school functions.\n\nEdit :I am glad we could speak to higher management on this issues and they have assured us issues will be sorted out so would love to give 3.5 till then. Nothing I have seen yet. I hope the school keeps transparency and keeps us parents in loop as it's out kids future at stake even though it may be just business for them.\n\nEdit Jan 12th: I am extremely sad I admitted so many kids with reference to this school so that it prospers and so does my son.  Never thought like  Bullying and teacher missing and education will go for toss. After several Bullying complaints the school , teachers and management have just turned blind eye. Missing teacher and rushing through portion without making sure kids have understood.\nVery very disappointed.",
